content: I really love this app. Made a lot of great friends. The people here are surprisingly friendly. Also, is it just me, but using the Keyboard in this app makes it slow down and lag. The keyboard stays in that lag for the rest of the time , unless I reboot the phone. This gboard doesn't get it from any other apps whilst typing. Please look into it. Currently I just type in Google Keeps, copy and paste it into the letter and send it. Since typing in the app makes it lag after a while.

Love the app it's pretty cool. But a few things could make it better and that is add different stationary to make it even more personal, be nice to add your actual photos or do the avatar, I'm a plus member but it still has a limit on how many letters I can send out wish that was not the case since I paid for the app. If all of this happens then I will give 5 stars. And if company is reading this thanks for reading my review.

This app is great, super fresh concept. The only reason I'm not giving 4 stars is cos of the bugginess when you type long messages - and in not even talking that long. Around 300 characters and above and it starts to get funky, the cursor jumps around. Also, it would be useful to have a language proficiency filter in the manual search, just like in auto match. If I want to speak to someone fluent in French but people of all levels show up, it's going to take a while to filter through them.

I really love this app since it helps me find language partners a lot easier than any other app! We can find each other not only by language we speak/are learning, but we can see how much we have in common and our interests! I've gotten so many language partners out of this app & it's wonderful to exchange letters at your own pace. My only complaint is I wish I could be more specific about the age range I want to filter through. I would like to pick people aged 23+ for similar lifestyle and age

Really cool idea, executed well, UI is great, moderation is great and the paid upgrades are really reasonable and totally optional. It's an odd feeling, because I'm probably more likely to participate in the paid model because it's actually cool stuff, and not because you're kindof forced to to get the full app experience. Well done all around.

I really enjoy this app. There's something relaxing and comforting about writing and waiting for letters. Plus, the stamps are pretty neat. I also really like how you can set reminders to reply to a letter, especially since I tend to get caught up with other important stuff IRL, like my studies. The devs are really helpful, as well. I reported a problem and they immediately went to fix it.

This app is amazing, but if the app developers are reading my review, I really want you the address the issue of Buggs when writing long letters and then those bugs just stays there in my keyboard until and unless I uninstall the app and reinstall. Once the letters starts bugging or i don't know what the exact problem is but then it becomes very difficult to write a single word because the cursors just goes flipping insane. And I have tried updating my software too. Please solve this issue.

Good app for people who wants to exp penpals digitally. I love the feature of waiting for the letter based on how far the person is to you. It has such a kind community as well. I love how we get to collect stamps but I was hoping it would include some mini games for us to get more coins easily, instead of getting 1 per ad~ Making the stamps more available to the Users would make the experience more exciting and fun~ üòä Atleast that's what I thought about making people more interactive here~

I like the app. It brings back the typical old-style of sending letters. Only difference is it is done online. Here you will get to know the person real well, his or her daily activities, his emotions and feelings without any judgement at all because your initial way of communication is through letters. It will be your choice to send photos. Though, it is frustrating sometimes to wait for the letters to arrive but that is where the excitement is! Really love it!

Love the app! This is by far my favorite penpal app/site I've ever used! Due to the wait time for letters to get delivered people tend to write more thoughtful messages than with instant messaging. One thing I would love to see added to make this app absolutely perfect is a feature where you could set a reminder to respond to a letter. When I can't write back right away I tend to forget so a reminder notification would be great! Other than that I can't reccomend this app enough, great job guys!

Clean interface, very easy to navigate I just started hiding everyone I'm not interested in while using my specific match filters and I think I found a bug where it shows 'no matches found' whenever I refresh manual matchmaking after hiding the first person. Whenever I would pick a specific country/region (my usual filter does not include any), the matches would load properly and disappear again once I switch to my usual filters. Please fix this

This is such a great way to connect with our fellow brothers and sisters around the world, especially at a time that we're in now with COVID-19. I have really enjoyed this app so far and I've received already some lovely letters! This app is easy to use and I would recommend it to anyone. I like how you can create an avatar and view where you'll be receiving a letter from. I can't say I've had any issues. Anyhow my name is PiscesChild if you'd like to connect with me. Absolutely fantastic app!

This app is really good.if you have any android,i wouldn't recommend downloading because whenever you type long letters,the keyboard or the app starts to lag and either one will eventually crash.this lag happens even more severely after you deleted the app on android only.this app is probably more biased towards ios, not too sure :/

Maybe i'll rate it 5 when you've increase the number of coins the users' get when they watch ads. This is an app that helps me connect with other people across the globe. I seriously love how the letters are sent just like the old days. However, like what i've state above, I don't really like the part when we literally just earn a single coin by watching an ad. I know putting a price on a coin is part of this business(?) stuff but hey how about us who doesn't have any money to buy coins?

When you set up your profile it automatically matches you with someone, but you have the option to turn it off. You also can filter people who send you messages by age and location,sort of. It sends it like regular mail times, sometimes taking a day or two for them to receive response, and from what I can tell, most don't respond to messages they get! You can see sent to receive rate and most don't reply back!

Nowadays when typing long letters the editor starts to get buggy. First I thought it was a problem with my phone, but it turns out my penpal had the same issue. Please fix this issue ASAP!!! It just ruins the whole experience

I've been using the app for 5 months now and it's great. Although I do have a few qualms. 1. A text based app has no reason to not have font/formatting option. That and markup support seem like basic feature they should include. 2. There are no statistics for total no of letters sent/received categorized by country which again seems like a basic feature to implement. 3. The web client has no matchmaking feature.

The concept of this app is clean and clear. But after update,sometimes the letters fails to get saved in cloud. That's the only little issue i faced. Other than that, I made many good friends on that app

I used to love the app and I still get notifications when people send me letters but it won't let me sign in after the 'update' it jsut says that there is no slowly acc with that name/number. And plus I know that no one else has my name so when I try and make a new acc it jsut says there is already an acc under the name. It hasnt deleted my account won't let me in!!!! Help?!

It's easy to use, anonymous, has no ads, and has a simple interface. It's a matter of taking incentives and reaching out to write letters first. I've gotten a few letters written back from different places and countries in the world. For safety matters, it's cool to see where people come from but it is concerning too (they said that the location was randomly adjusted though). And honestly, the content in the letters I've read where mainly about life.

Probably the best meeting, and getting to know people app around! No false people! It has a decent number of active users across the globe! Promotes long and meaningful discussion! And it's actually free! I would give it 5/5 but it does have it's down sides and places for improvement. Updates will often cause app to have crashes and freezes, although as it does save what you write both locally and on the cloud you are unlikely to lose much more than a last few sentences you wrote when it happens

A must app for someone who likes to write letters and meeting new people. I promise this app won't disappoint you. You can find lots a people with the same interest and have interesting conversation through letters. The wait makes it worth it. Over all this app deserves a 5 star from me because I have met some really wonderful people through this app.

I love the concept and design of the app. Well done to the developers. This is great way to communicate with real people. There's beauty behind waiting for an incoming letters. Breaking the norm of instant messaging.
I love this! I'm so thankful only matches people in your age range and you can't send photos and recordings immediately. I'd suggest adding more hairstyles and clothes, but that's a nitpick really.

Very fun and nostalgic feel. I have made a few friends who I intend to keep but it's a shame when some of them flicker out, but that's life. The app is discreet [because if you choose not to answer back the sender is none the wiser] and easy to maneuver around. Its fulfills its use perfectly.

You can write letters to different people and gets delivered slowly, 24 hrs+. Can change options to show you certain results, i.e, what gender, country, etc and can choose users to write to. You cant add a real pic of yourself and can't see pics of others. Can send about 8 messages per day

Hey guys some letters are taking more time than what's said, letters of one day take 30 hours. Plus it keeps bugging on long letters. Please fix that, mainly the time that letters take. I hope it is fixed soon because I like the app.

This app is so cool. Having a pen pal is really fun! Some people might think that instant messaging is easier, but there's just something special about waiting for a message from a friend. It teaches you to be more patient.

I literally cannot get past the terms of service to even enjoy the app at all, I click to read the terms of service and privacy and that's as far as it goes there's nothing on the page to click to keep going further into the app to even play with it
I feel this is a great app, so far. However, I feel it could be a bit quicker with the mail, maybe few hours for a letter to send. But it takes almost a day and a half just to send a letter.

Best of its kind. A varying arrival time depending on location adds authenticity while a crisp and aesthetic yet simple design allows easy navigation. Create a unique avatar with Slowly's broad selection of virtual accessories and earn cute stamps to add flair to letters. Get suggestions, filter, or send letters to unknown people. You are bound to find friendship with this app's diversity. However, a dark theme is desirable since this is a pen pal app in which reading/writing is prominent.

It's been very long since I wrote to anyone or poured thought into constructing topics for strangers. And this is actually the first time that I could lie back and wait for a response after a dishing of words from anyone in the world, even in my country. The function is so simple but really efficient. Snail mail, I never even dealt with before but I'n glad this app was made to relieve that pain of waiting so long for any response. The matching feat's a big pp concept. Thanks, devs.

content: Really like the app but here's a few things. 1. 1 gold for 1 adds is too less 2. Ads doesn't even appear, it shows N/A everytime 3. At the profile, the sent/received is always bugged and stays at 1:1.
Overall a great app. People are friendly and the slowness of the letters lead to actual conversation. The app design is great. I haven't had any problems at all. 5/5

Slowly have the power to bring the peoples together around the world. Here your friendship are unexpected and the unexpected friendship are the best one beyond distance , shape, size and colour cos here you don't see the real profile picture of your penpals but there is option of sharing pictures and audio messages when your pal agree with this As the name slowly tell about himself the pens delivers on the basis of distance and takes a bit time so you have not addicted to this app like others .

I truly enjoy this app. I do have a few suggestions. Can you add a "wishlist" or something to the app. There are so many interesting people to write to, that one search through the descriptions and before you know it you lose a person you wanted to write to.
I like the concept of this, I allows you to have an old school style of meeting someone but I wished there was an option to make custom stamps.
It's nice and simple. I've made several good friends across the world, we swap letters, comment each others instagrams etc.. I like it.
I love it. I love the anticipation. I am appreciative and grateful for the awesome friends I've made. Amazed that I've heard from people all over the world. I especially had fun with the heist Boss.

I have never rated any app 5/5.. And this is my first ever comment on any app. Most wondeful app I ever have. Sometimes the waiting phase is irritating but that's okay.. It truly gives you that excitement of an ancient time üòÑ

I have really enjoyed meeting folks from around the world with similar passions. I like that I must wait to send/receive like they are real letters. I enjoy letters. The stamps are a nice touch as well. Great for meeting people and chatting in these crazy days we live in. I have been brushing up on languages as well as practicing a new language with willing penpals all while discussing things we have in common. Love this app!
Like the concept behind but the app frequently crashes. Kindly work on this. I'd like to enjoy the experience of letter writing more.

I think this is a good idea, I used to have pen pals and this is similar. The only thing is that there's some problem with the app because sometimes it freeze and I am unable to write or send anything.
Its a really good app but I wish you didn't have to pay to send letters to more than 10 people. Other then that its really great and I've had a lot of fun on it!
I love this app but sometimes it takes forever to load. It would be great favor to do for the users if this problem gets fixed.
A really good app. I just hope it would give us a push notification if there's a new stamp (especially the limited edition ones), but overall I like the improvements!
Interesting, this app can be good to help language learners who in the current climate can't travel to other countries to study language but also just to meet some interesting people.
I think it's a nice concept to get a feel of how communication took place in earlier times. We get an idea of that excitement to read the letter after a wait.
The app is just amazing! Kudos to all the efforts by the developers to make it as close to the real life pen friend concept as possible!

It's good app, but somewhat dead. Not very many people on it who respond to letters. It'd be nice if you received an email whenever you get a letter, especially because notifications don't always work.

I love this app because it combines snail mail with modern technology! It's a fun way to connect with people!

Lots of fun. Really enjoying the app so far. Features are all good.

Great app. Meet some amazing and kind people through letters.

This is by far the best app I've seen where I could make friends with people all around the world. The best part is.....this app eliminates unwanted VIDEO CALL OPTIONS OR UNSOLICITED, INAPPROPRIATE PHOTOS OR CALLS! This is something I love abou this app. I've recommended this to so many people and all have loved It too. Moreover, this is so much needed in these times when we are getting desperate and the idea of writing letters, waiting for them, writing back.....everything is just so amazing!

It's an interesting concept and one I have been enjoying since day one. You sign up, fill your profile with a bio, interests, and an avatar, and find people to connect with from anywhere. You can add some filters or be automatically matched based on interests. When someone sends you a letter, you get notified who it is, where it's coming from (a general area for privacy), and how long until you receive it. You can't read it ahead of time which is part of the fun and appeal! Highly recommended!

I really love this app, it's such an innovative idea. The problem is with the recent update, it claims to have increased the app performance in contrary it has only made it worse. It takes soo long for the application to load to its home page, even though the friend list is listed out it takes much longer for the letters to load, the whole application lags. I'd request the team to fix this as soon as possible. Otherwise the app is justüî•.

Perfect for those who are tired of instant communication. You can send people photos and voice messages as well but they will also get delivered slowly given the time it takes for a letter to reach its destination. Audience of the app is mainly quite different and it is always fun sending and receiving letters. App has dark mode too. My only concern is not being able to block people once you delete them forever.

The concept is great honestly, but the technical side of things always gives me issues. I have a phone with great characteristics and the app will still start lagging when I'm writing a letter every single time with no exception. It's disappointing, because I would've definitely given this app 5 stars, had the issues been solved in the last 6 months of their constant presence.
So far so good, although I wish that there was a way for us to speed up the delivery of a letter üíõ
Hello! People at SLOWLY thanks for this great app but can you add an apology stamp, I think I might need it soon.

I really do love this app. It gives such an amazing opportunity to meet others in a way I have yet to see any other app offer. No creepy messages, no spam, it's amazing. The only recommendation I have is to make letters more personalized through new fonts, stickers, different paper options, etc. I think it could really take it from being a great app to a perfect app--thank you! ‚ô•Ô∏è

So far this app seems to be a great idea! It could use some performance improvements but overall it's such a unique and wholesome concept. I have been written letters from two people so far and I love the longer form way of writing that has been lost since technology has taken over. Also, the fact that you don't get the letter instantly means you can write less often and about things that actually matter/hold interest. Definitely recommend.

I have only been using the app for a few days now and it's been fun! I do wish you could put a filter on user so you are sure to only get people who use the app as often as you do. I personally super like this app even though I just started joining here. The reason it lacks one more star is that there is one flaw about this app. It lags. I'm a 15 year old girl but have 20 year old men messaging me. Apart from that, I love this app so much and have met many lovely people! Highly recommend!

I love it! I love the concept and I'm glad I've met new people c:

I love the idea of the app and the design. This is the best App I ever downloaded!üòÉ I started using this last year and now I had a friend. I love the idea of talking with someone from the other side of the world. Your app is really awesome. I enjoy the concept and everything. But this app have a major issue and that is opening this app. Why does it take so much time to load. And even after opening it takes even much time to open the letters. Sending opening everything takes too much time. What is the problem? Hope you guys can solve this issue very soon.

I used to love this app and was really happy to pay for stamps additionally. Now they have become greedy and want you to subscribe for 9‚Ç¨ a month for a "pro" experience with barely any extra features, and you still have to buy stamps separately. This is WAY overpriced. i'm giving five stars though i have little nit to pick. when writing a really long letter, my tablet tends to lag a lot. and this is every single time. i figured that maybe my tablet was in the wrong, but when i typed outside of the app, it never lagged. other than that, this app is perfect. i made a great friend on here.

This is such a great app for a polyglot, someone interested in foreign culture, or someone whithout fondness for the pressures of instant messaging ‚Äì but still prefers the modernity of phones. The avatar customization is fun too! You can really go in depth and write a lengthy bio or keep it simple and just select tons of interests, which will help match you with a pen pal. I'm so impressed.

Not easy to understand and navigate. But there is a FAQ that you can look at. It's a great idea and I like the idea of the old school pen pals of letters and not just short texts. It's really great that it takes a long time for the letter to arrive and someone needs to request to send you pictures and vice versa. I love the idea of the avatars and nicknames.

This app is great for connecting with people from all over the world. The only thing I wish this app has is a way to temporarily prevent new people from writing to you. It's getting to the point where I'm starting to get overwhelmed with the amount of letters I'm receiving. I don't want to not respond to anyone, and I want to be able to give each reply the attention it deserves. I'd like to focus on the people I'm already talking with, and temporarily take a break from getting new letters.

I am loving this app so far - I'm meeting people from all over and finding the platform very simple to use. I think the stamps should be awarded more quickly, perhaps as rewards for a certain number of letters reached or similar, as I would appreciate the variety.

Can we please introduce auto save? C'mon, it's 2020 even MS has got auto save. Love the concept and of course the mustard theme of the UI. It's just beautiful. I think you could use some conformity in the art//design tho. The thick black rectangles (for example: the one on the letter box thingie inside the yellow box and the hair/eyewear for avatars) I find from time-tt aren't very easy on the eyes. Idk how it factors in on the experience and if it's intended but personally, it's bit bothersome.

Super nice app. This is so good!!! Matching with pals with the same interests so you'll never get bored and it's nice to have that feeling of receiving a letter. It's an amazing app for those who wanna make friends around the globe... totally smooth and easy going app...I would highly recommend this to everyone out there....just install, make a profile and enjoy this slowly mailing app...the longing for the reply makes this app more special in this fast moving world...I'm totally in love with it...!!!

I love this idea. Edit: that's it . It's a lovely idea and it's very enojable. I also like how you can choose your interests so you can compare and find similar interests with others and automatically have something to talk about.

This app is fun you get to write letters to people around the world. But sadly after a while many penpals just fall off, I guess don't enjoy writing letters as much these days. A good idea would be to add a messaging system on the app as well, for easier and quicker communication.

I really like Slowly. I've used lots of apps for connecting with people from all over the world and practicing my language skills but this one is definitely different to all the apps I've tried so far. Just one suggestion, it'd be great if I could find my drafts in both my computer and my phone because I've started typing a draft on my computer but when I wanted to continue typing it on my phone I couldn't find it.

If you can add password function to open the apps, it will be awesome I love it the idea. Bring me back of those memories. Hand writing a letter, waiting for postman, buying a post card in when I was on travel, excited to tell what happen in my life. Give me a "mask" to be free make friends and speak up with foreigner. It's ideal for introvert, but I'm sure extrovert will like it too.

Great idea and great execution overall, but some things need to change, e.g. the quality of "matches" (a person who shares only 1 of my interests most definitely isn't a match). Also, the sent:received ratio is useless other than adding a needless competitive element to the app.

This is probably the best discovery I've ever made. I've been looking for this kind of app for a long time and finally here it is. I love how it works. Here I can truly express myself with my writings and learn new things with people. I love its purpose which is very decent in a way. And I get to meet awesome writers, readers, professionals and a lot more people that shares the same concepts, ideas, and beliefs like mine. Thank you for creating this app.

its a fun app for people who want to make friends around the world, I myself have learned so much. though I have been having trouble responding to some people, its not that i am over the limit, i only have like 9 friends, there isn't an option to respond and i really want to. I'm sorry if I was to say this somewhere else, i didn't see.

It's a really nice app, but I have some suggestions. It would be great if we could personalize more the letters, like adding color to the paper and draw on it or changing the color of the text, adding stickers on it. I get the app is like minimalistic but I would loveeee to make my letters with more personality!

This app has nice concept. I have been looking for an app like this. It give you 80's vibes which take long to deliver letter and I love it! It makes me cherish the letters. I also like that it won't reveal the name, can't send pictures unless the other one agree.

So far it's been a great experience. I like getting replies from those that do reply. It's frustrating when people don't because you wait so long and then eventually realize they aren't interested in talking or don't use the app anymore. I have had some interesting conversations though!

After all of the updates and modifications of the app I would say it has added a few practical features to it. However! the typing experience has been rendered to downright annoying. Previously before all of that I did not have absolutely any issue in typing down what I wanted how I wanted. Now instead of that I have to fear if it'll start lagging as I write down, and start cutting while paragraphs as I have had them already written down.Thereare a fewmoreissuesIwant totouchupon but symbol limit

I love the app because it is totally different from what we have these days. But i have a problem, you guys logged me out and i have sent a mail as requested. I just found a pen pal and i wait daily to get her letters. Now i can't get that opportunity to wait for it anymore. Please do something about it.

I really like it. It's very fun and very thrilling to wait for a letter. Can I give just one recommendation and if it is possible that when you are filtering by interested topics, can the only ones appearing be selected ones and not in just a few like 1/3 interests or 2/3 . What I mean that if you selected 3 topics only those 3 topics match and not just a few. Also can you change the send letter to just 1 day instead lf 2 days because it feels really tiring reading some letters 2 days later.
Somehow, I was able to fix my issue, though I would like the developers to create a system, an ad system perhaps, so one can get exclusive stamps..

SLOWLY is like a travelling back time into the 90s where sending and receiving messages are slow but the depth of the message is real! People people don't have the option to upload or sent images, which XBQKMW should keep it that way for shy individuals like me... later we can approve the other person whether to sent more attachments or stay pen-pal via this digital letter writing format. I highly encourage people nowadays to use this as it really trains our patience and creative writing skills!

It's a great app, just a few recommendations for the next update. More options for customizing avatars. More ways to personalize letters you send, like changing color of the text or the letter, adding different fonts, etc. Also adding more topics and add subtopics to each.

Really fun app, great concept, though I wish it was better optimised for tablets. For example, during registration, the on-screen keyboard wouldn't stay on screen. Also, it can't rotate easily in all directions. Still, I love this app, great work!

I really like the idea of this app. It can be educational and gives something to look forward to. It's also a great place to meet new people from all around the world. My one wish is for the age filter to be more exact! For example instead of 0-20 I wish I could pick one age to be matched with.

Slowly is a great app for connecting with others around the world:). Sure, it takes longer than it usually would to send or receive a message or letter via your cell phone, but that's the point of the app. It's a pen pal system. I absolutely love it. It's so much funüòÜ.

Amazing app to talk to good strangers, appreciate the efforts. Though waiting time is a bit high, when we want to talk to strangers from other side of the world, If that can be reduced to a nominal time, app is perfectly fine. As most of us would want to speak to people from other part of the world but we would be anxious to get a reply ASAP in the era of WhatsApp and snapchat.

This app is amazing but one star so it doesn't get lost in the good reviews, the biggest issue is when typing letters it lags so much it slows down my phone and makes typing my letter impossible, other ppl have had this issue. I'd also like a swiping feature on the manually search for penpals and better avatar looks but those are only wishes. That bug needs to be fixed so ppl can enjoy the app the way it should be.

I rarely leave reviews but if you're bored and looking to find new people over the internet THIS is the way to go. I've tried out other apps and websites before but this one matched me with interesting, communicative people who actually wanted to try and have a conversation or become friends. There's even a matching filter if you want to use it. I left the app running for day and soon people were matching and sending letters. I've already made two or three friends so you should def try this app!

Easy to use and connect with people. Love the idea of slower communication and keeping people connected without instant messenger. It would be good to see more topics added over time. Maybe even voice notes. On the whole a good app and enjoyable to use!

App is an great concept!Today,instant messaging services and social medias,relation between pros seem a bit shallow and the addicting nature due to instant gratification does not seem to help.Slowly has simplr and user-friendly interface,clean functioning(sometimes it takes a long time to load) and really great Auto-match algorithm.I hope that the concept gets more deserved attention but doing so by keeping the original concept intact.

Its a really good app that lets you meet nice people. Been using this for a year. I highly suggest it to people who are looking for deep convos, and slow paced writing. Suggestion: why not create multiple themes? Like, Dark theme? Black and blue? To make it grungy.

Such a fantastic idea and well thought out. I have met some incredibly nice and genuine people on here, from all across the world! To hear people ask me advice on learning English is so much fun, and I've done the same with learning other languages myself. What is so unique about this app is how engaging the culture is, people seem to WANT to have authentic conversations. People put effort in actually getting to know you. I love this app.

Awesome app for meeting new people from all parts of the world. Everyone here is so polite amd nice. I also like the fact that messages take some time to deliver and receive like a real letter. It's convenient so that we can think ahead of what to write in our next letter.

I used to use Slowly a lot more than I do now mainly because people stopped sending me interesting letters to respond to and whenever I send letters, no one responds... but before that happened the app worked as it advertised, had a nice interface, it worked well. It was fun to use.

Wow, the web app doesn't automatically save drafts. I spent a long time writing a letter and closed my browser, losing everything. This needs to be changed. What an awful thing to have as a default setting. It should save every five minutes or so, like every other composition tool on earth???? What a shame, in 2020.

I really like this app. Exchanging letters with people around the globe and waiting to get a reply is new and exciting experience. A way of communication that is not judged by the way the person look like but with how you exchange interesting topics with mutual interest.

Should put a feature for people must put a stamp on each letter, not just the slowly stamp. It will visually give the same vibe as a real letter which needs a stamp before sending a letter. Also, it will make people more excited to buy the stamp on the store as they need to put a stamp. Don't you say you want to put a limited usage on a stamp? Making people taking care more on the stamp on each letter would be nice.

I loved this app so much! Felt like I experienced sending post mail again. I kind of missing it. I never thought that I would wait that long to read letters from a new friend. This app can improve more but for now this app really got me. Thank you!

I love this app so much. The letter/mail concept is wonderful. I've made so many friends around the planet in like 1-2 weeks üòÖ also, if you don't feel like finishing a letter, you can just close it and it'll save it for you. The stamp collection thing is really cute.

Really enjoy meeting new ppl from all around the world. I gave 4 stars instead of 5 because even though you meet & talk to new people, sometimes it might only be for a few conversations, it would be nice if people would commit to a long term "pen pal" relationship. Overall still like it a lot.

Really cool app! New experiences to be had and fun times to be made. Only downside is sometimes I don't always get notifications when I've received a letter. Not sure if it's the app or my phone though. Highly recommended for anyone looking for pen pals!
Hello everyone, this app is too interesting! It enables any one to communicate to a friend every where in the world. It's perfect!üôèüôèüòç

I'm new to this but so far it actually does interest me. The whole thing about not being swamped with notifications requiring responses is cool. Plus, there is the opportunity to get into meaningful conversations here at your pace. Nice idea for an app.

It is an amazing app! Great way to meet people and make friends from around the world! In my book I would say this is a successful app. The people you meet are so down to earth, humble, nice, caring, and kind. I would want everyone to try this app if they would want someone to talk to or make a friend üòÉüëç

A unique app that gives the newer generation (Me) a taste of what letters were like. On top of that is a wonderful system of discovering new people through shared interests and hobbies. Overall, I love the app and already have a few pen pals!

I use this app from last year. But the latest update (when slowly desktop appear), the slowly in my android is so laggy, can't type properly because of the laggy. Then i always use the desktop version to reply all the letters. But this is not always convenient. I will re review if the issue has been fixed.

Best app outthere.. It helps you to meet a lot of people around the globe and be friend with them‚ù§Ô∏è.. I feel tthere should be an option to fast deliver your msg if the recipient has no problem with it.. I would love to see this feature.. If both people agree to see the letter faster then there should be an additional chat system in slowly

The one downside is that there are a few times people don't respond at all, but that's just how it is sometimes. Give it a try and see how great it is yourself.

The idea of the app is very fun and unique. The app itself does need lots of improvement though. Sometimes its getting laggy when your letter is getting long, or sometimes it doesnt fully save a draft letter. But I'll give it time cuz i've been enjoying the app a lot

I've been so in love with Slowly since 2018 September, and still a loyal user that buys stamps every once in awhile. And to people who find it difficult to write back letter, I suggest you just copied the previous letter you're replying into your note app and then write in that app instead of directly in Slowly, when you finish, you can just cut it and paste to your Slowly page and then click send. That way you don't have to worry about the lagging issue. Happy writing!

Its really good app ... If you likes to make friends all around the world in degital pen-pal way ..than this is the best app available in play store ... Cool stamps , good avatar edits , and good filters that can let u meet your new penpals around the world with your requrments ..what other things needed?!!! So go for it

Great app! Net good friends. Yes the letters take a while to deliver, but it makes it more exciting! U wait for letters and value them instead of just talking for an hour and never again. The stamps r expensive though. Maybe if there was a way to earn coins?

i'll rate this app, 4 stars. so far so good, the fact that it brings back those times in the past where all u can do is send a letter someone then they'll receive in a few days, so you have to make it worth the wait. i found a few interesting friends here!

I love this app. It helps you connect people acrosa the globe, and the idea of communicating using letters is unique and amazing. The time it takes to deliver letters, if only it had been reduced, the app would really be worth 5 stars for me.üòä

I don't like the sent: received ratio. I don't understand why it was there in the first place. I downloaded this app to talk to people and make new friends and in order to do that I HAVE to send letters out in order to communicate and there are lots of people I wanna send letters too but the other people may look at your ratio and judge it and it might make them wanna respond less or not even start communication with you. I just don't like it.

It's a good app to make friends and to learn new things. My suggestion is that add a language translator engine because some are hard to communicate in English. And please, lessen the time interval in sending & receiving letters haha üòÑ. Thanks!

It's a good way to meet new people from different countries and to start new friendships. The anticipation gets real sometimes XD. Only wish that there'd be a way to earn coins, especially for new ones like me. It's still a very good app, overall.

I get the whole waiting for a response is the entire point of this app, but it just gets kinda annoying and boring after a while. There's nothing wrong with the app in the sense that it does exactly what it's meant to. Just don't expect to make any deep meaningful connections any time soon.

this app has a really great idea in mind but the execution is really wanting. it's really buggy especially if your letters go past a certain point then it really lags and stops working all together. it really would have been a really great app had all the bugs been fixed :(

This is a great app for getting out of your shell; you can find people specific of gender, age, zodiac, interests, and destination! However, a page somewhere in the app to look at some conversation starters would be a nice touch!

I've found one of my best friends via this app! There's an option to try and write a letter to a random person chosen by computer (based on interests), and he ended up writing me üòÇ obviously there's a lot of people you don't end up having a connection with, but if you're willing to try, you'll find a friend for life üôåüèª

No ads, lots of options in the settings. I live in the US; it takes, most of the time, 1 day for your letter to reach who you're sending it to so it feels like a legitimate pen-pal. Great app, great experience.

I loved Slowly ever since I first installed it! The thing is...typing on my phone is so troublesome, I really wish a pc version comes out. I would answer and type my letters much easily! For now, I will stick to good ole synced note pad to copy and paste what I type on my laptop haha.

I don't know if you can pin it down to living in a world of short form communication, creative writing style (or lack thereof) or maybe it's just me, but all are in play. You have to hook your penpal with a good story every time or its short lived. I see the word "depression" being used often for topics on penpals profiles and can see why. I'm often depressed using this app and didn't feel that way prior to joining. 99% of my contacts have been short term. I'm still trying, foolishly.

Best app to express yourself. Being an Introvert and old school this app helps me to be myself! I hope this stays forever and doesnt get polluted by cheesy predators! I hope the creator will not mind me saying that it has to be protected to limited users and thanks to you the one who made this. Looking forward to connect with more like minded Wanted to give 5 stars one star less for the keyboard when i type a letter i feel something is disturbing me!

This app is so unbelievable.... Its just stopped working began to ask me when you use the app for z first time.... I did all thing things that asked me before but then all people that i was talking to disappear like the app before u log in...... I just can't understand why this happen it was great app i was going to give it 5 star but then, noooo....
It more slow than its name.

- I like that avatars replace photos to imitate snail mail - neat design and lovely stamps - I wonder if other users also find the default empty stamp useless? I mean, each user has a couple of local country stamps available in any case. I'd rather get letters with those than a blank S stamp please:)

The app is awesome! AWESOME! Just somethings I wanted to share that's when writing a long letter, the app came slower, becoming difficult to write the end of letter. Despite this, it's one of the best apps I've ever seen!

This app is great for anyone who loves penpalling! The only thing I would mention is that I wish there were a way to delete letters from the main screen, while still being able to access them under penpal profiles. I also wish there were an option to see only unopened mail.

It's a really cool app for finding a penpal. It works like old letter writing and it takes about a day or two for your message to be delivered based on the distance. Also, you can stamp your letters. So vintage. Love it

It's an amazing way to meet new friends, instead of looking at each other's photo before saying anything. UI is simple, clean, and easy to navigate. The people I have been writing to are nice and friendly so far. Definitely recommend this app!

There can't be better app than this to find genuine people and connect. First reason being the spammers are out of picture since the letter delivery takes time and the people who take time I'm lengthy and meaningful letters can't waste their time spamming you they are the genuine people. I have found my genuine penpals and have written many letters. This helps me improve a lot personally. Thanks for the creators. And definitely this app is for those who exhibit patience.!

I made an account yesterday, logged in, and tried to strike up a conversation with a person from a different country, because that's what you do, right? Well, I log in today only to see that my account has been locked for absolutely no reason. One day of usage and I didnt even have a conversation with anyone. Terrible user experience.

This app is great! Infact the best i've come across. But i do have a problem. This app is slowing my phone down. App lags a lot and even after i exit it is slowing my phone down for some time. Maybe you should fix the lag.

A very good app to connect to people around the world. You won't find any fake profiles here because it takes a day for a letter to be received. The best thing about this app is it contains No ads. Surely one of the best apps on play store.

It's really fun there, you meet new people, I have so many friends now and you can really think what you want to say to them, since I'm not very talkative I don't say so much and I use emoticons to show my emotions more and they appreciate it, I like the people there they are very nice, I'm so happy I gave this app a chance when I stumbled over it here

This app really brings out the sort of "traditional" vibe and true meaning of communication. Its been awhile since I last felt very excited over waiting for a reply. The art is cute and it's very easy to use once you get the hang of it.

Best app to meet people. But people abandon us in-between and we are not able to know if they have removed us or not. One star deduction for removing last seen 24 hour filter and not providing International Yoga Day Stamp. It would be better if an app is available for Windows also.

I've only had this app for a couple of days but I already LOVE it! The interface is very easy to use and I've already made multiple friends from multiple countries~ I highly encourage downloading, you won't find a better penpal app!

There's just one problem in this app. And that is a major issue. As soon as the length of the letters increase, typing becomes very hard because it starts hanging. Haven't you guys designed it to handle long letters? This really sucks.

In case you don't know, the app's name is "slowly" for a reason üòÇüòÇ It's slow üòÇüòÇ But I really don't understand why the letters would take a day to send üòñ it's not friendly for users who wants to write to foreigners from afar (it's really not "connect to the world") I don't want to wait for 24+ hours just for sending 1 letter to my homeland...

Good concept. Main problems: I have trouble getting into the app as it takes forever to load. Often when the letter is lengthy, the application slows down and/or crashes. Will re-rate once problem is fixed.

A really great app. Here you can find pen pal from around the world. The feature which dont send mail directly is really awesome. That way it is like experiencing real mail. Really recommend this app. You can find many kind of person around the world

This app is awesome. I have given a five star. But does it have dark mode. I think it would be better if it also adds dark theme. Do, take a look at my comment. Anyways, besides this I love this app very much. Thanks for bringing this up.

Instantly fell in love with it. This is not a dating app. But if you like the snail mail way of communication with people not from the fast walks of life....you will love this for sure. Wish if there is some basic text cutomization tools

Such a creative concept! I get really excited for the letters and the design of the app is really cute too! The only drawback might be people using it as a messaging app with their short, generic messages :/ Maybe a word count meter could help?

I love it! I've found many great people to connect with in genuine and interesting ways. Combined with that, the app is easy to use and designed well, with matching browser access which also works well.

This app is unique. I have all the positive things to say about it. Connected to wonderful people and also let go of some amazing friends. The bittersweet experience has compelled me to write the review here. At times cursor goes very slow. Please work on it.

I have seen no flaw in the app except, it would be perfect if : I want to receive letters only from a specific number of countries, but that's not possible. I only can exclude 5 countries maximum. Thank you.

A very unique approach to relive the past. The waiting for the letter to send and recieve, the stamp collecting feature. Loved it. It‚Äôs like reliving the golden age of letters in this century again.

Reminds us that era where no internet no telephones exist and our elders made friends by writing just a letter. Pen friend culture returns with new look. Thanks to the developers for giving us the opportunity to have the experience how it feels by making new friends by writing letters.

I thought that the time it takes to send/receive letters would be annoying, but I honestly appreciate it. I don't feel rushed to respond and I have more time to think out what to type. It makes me less anxious than other friendly messaging apps

I love sending and receiving letters but Covid has pretty much put an end to that. This app is so great for helping with my second languages and making new friends. Wish I had found it earlier during the lockdown.

I've been using this app for a few days, and I love it. I thinks it's a fantastic concept. However, sometimes when I open the app it gets stuck on the loading screen. The only solution I've found is to uninstall and re-install the app, but it's quite inconvenient.

This app is a wonderful idea. I have made unforgettable friends from different countries and learnt a lot. I like the anticipation that comes with waiting for a response from a friend. It's made the lockdown interesting.

I love that you added local storage because the app does crash sometimes without autosaving to cloud. I wish y'all would add either a word limit or fix the length of letter you can write before your keyboard is malfunctioning. A more specific age filter is still welcome!

The app is the reason for the best thing that has happened to me. I have been using this for the past 2 years and it's been a really good experience. I got to meet lots of wonderful people, learn new things about different places and all. Most of all I found the love of my life through Slowly and next month we celebrate our first anniversary. My sincere gratitude.

Have been using it for some time, have to say it, it's a neat concept. The app is a joy to use, and I would like to thank the developers for bringing the long lost art of pen pals and letter writing to the smartphone platform. Keep going!

Wonderful experience, better than any other instant communication app. We can express our feeling as letter to someone and wait for their reply is most interest thing in this app. Old postal concept is wonderful. I love this app very much

Wonderful concept. I love that cartoonish avatar of me most. It has offers me to revive my old habit of letter writing. I met some wonderful human being. Some suggestion if avatar can be modified 2 times and if auto signaure can be appended.

Niceeee i have tons of friends already here but can plss add more styles in the character so we can change some dress thanks üòäüòä

I've really enjoyed this app. Met some cool ppl, made a couple friends... And if you want more you can always move from here. But it's fun to write letters and have the anticipation of the wait. Lol üòä

Truly an awesome app, I've met so many wonderful people via this platform and if i may be so bold..its a suggestion, perhaps the devs could create a sort of buzz or pinging system to be able to ring a long lost penpal. A great app all in all

This is very good app. People are very friendly and you have good chances to get new friends. Slowly is slow but it's better than other fast services. It makes real connection and Patience. Try it, this is best.
Great app. Very good for those who want to connect with others from other countries in a different way then texting.

This is a really great app, the user interface is simple and the concept is very appealing. However, once the letter gets long, the app starts to become laggy and you cannot type very well. I rate this 4/5

It's an great app... its just I think we all are very lonely these... mostly depressed... we would like to talk to the people we feel connected. It took a long time to deliver the msg. Is it possible to reduce the time just till the pandemic end..? It would be awesome

The latest version is just so perfect... The concept, the design, the execution.. loved it.. best app of its kind..
Lovely way to meet people who are interested in proper conversations. Would like a few more options (maybe keywords?) to find people with more similar interests, but other than that it's amazing :)

It is really fun and amazing to be able to talk to people anonymously and talk anything random. This app helps me reconnect to different people around the world and I am loving the idea of having a 'pen pal'. Thank you so much.
Really good app to meet someone new.

an amazing app with amazing peoples in it from around the world.im a bit shy but I have already found 5 friends, wish me luck :3 just 2 minor problems 1 :I know it's more realistic to not be able to make change or delete your letter after you've send it but it might break relationships at list give us an hour to change the sent letters 2:I know it's also the main concept of this app but it would be better to be a little faster i mean 2 from me and 2 day from him 4 day waiting.its alot I guess
Nice app. Wish I could narrow search down more.
Not only does the app has a beautiful interface, it also works effortlessly. What I particularly like is that the app lets us explore and target people we'd like to send letters to manually.
I'm loving the app and the idea but there's bugs or something i think. After some time it starts to hang. And it's also affecting my phone's overall performance. Please fix it ASAP.

This is such a cool app! The concept and execution have been done very well. My only suggestion is to improve the automatic friend finder - right now it just seems to find people who speak your language and have (at least?) one mutual interest.
