Super easy and completely free to use, love the entire concept. I've found quite a number of people to talk to who I otherwise never would have met, and seeing notifications that I have replies or new letters arriving from a new friend is quite exciting. The match system allowing me to automatically match with new penpal or manually pick someone to send a message to is a great way to get conversations started, and the time between letters being sent and received really encourages me to put some thought into my letters and replies. Only thing I would suggest is to add a little more customisation of avatars as the options are currently limited to a white person with grey or yellow hair, and some people may feel that doesn't really represent them well, especially people with dark skin.

I really love the concept of this app! Even though it feels harder to actually find people to talk to, I like that it works at such a slow pace and I guess that's just a matter of time. But there's one problem: I accidently hid a letter while it was sending. Now it shows that I got a new letter, but it appears nowhere, so that I can't read it or do something against that "new message" notifcation.

Amazing app. Through this, we get to relive the old days when people used to wait for letters. Not only we connect to people across the globe, but we also get to experience the excitement of waiting for someone's reply. I feel that this is a must-have for those who want to explore new horizons the old-fashioned way. Extremely beautiful and simple UI and an amazing stamp collection features make it the only social connectivity app of its kind Superb job done!!!üòÅüòçü§©

The app is really cute, really simple and really fun. I use it most days and I feel like I can write what's on my mind and not feel attacked as everyone who I have met so far is kind and understanding. The idea behind the app is good and I like that it takes some time for the letters to send; you feel much more excited when you get a letter this way. Some people have criticized how long it takes but I think it's not too bad. I have only one complaint: there are some bugs and latency issues in the "arriving mail" screen. Sometimes it says you have letters incoming, sometimes it doesn't and even though you know you have mail it doesn't show up? On top of this, the "sent/recieved" ratio indicator on one's profile is often inaccurate or doesn't update quickly. Other than these bugs, it is a great app!

This *is* the exact penpalship experience that I've been looking for. Slowly is never about building your digital image and comparing it with others' (which too often leads to envy and anxiety), like on Instagram or Tinder. You don't even get to see a picture of your penpal at first (and neither do they see yours), and this prevents Slowly from devolving into a shallow dating app. Slowly is all about the conversation, and it's designed to give you the security you need to be open and honest.

This is a great app to discover new people across the globe. A little suggestion if i may, maybe you can cut the waiting time in half or maybe reduce it just a little bit because its a little ridiculous. I mean yeah its kinda realistic in a way but some people dont have the patience and they're going to stop using this app eventually because of the amount of time that they have to wait for a new letter is too long. But overall its a great app, simple, and very easy to use. Maybe you can add more profile character options too? Also maybe you can add more topics to the "interested topics" and add things that are more specific?

I love this idea. Very interesting. Very attractive to people born in the 1980s or before, and will be inspiring to younger generations too. If there is two things to be improved, one is the graphics (You may add some texture to the "paper" and colors to the stamps. And You could let people choose fonts that look not like handwriting too.) Another is that you may not need to show the "status" of the deliveries or notify us when letters are arriving, making the experience even more genuine. Thanks for the good work, people.

Awesome idea, amazing experience but needs some control tweaks including gestures control Along with some intuitive things like what should happen on back button press and on certain screens what should b way for going to a related other screen.
I really liked this app. Its not like the regular instant messengers out there. It values our privacy and keeps things exciting. Giving it 5 stars because I dont find any flaws.

I love the idea. However, the app is not intuitive enough. It feels buggy. I don't know why, but I navigate this app slowly (pun intended). Maybe it's not optimised for my phone? But this is a simple chat app, not resource heavy online game, therefore should not be laggy. I don't lag as much when playing games. Also, please add the ability to add topics ourselves. There are many things to talk about, yet slowly only covers so much topics.

love this app. ive always loved the idea of a pen pall and now i have them! its easy to use, and fun. i dont like how it doesnt show people the topics you do not want to talk about, it gives you the option to select topics you dont want to talk about or are not comfortable talking about yet people cannot see those so they still end up bringing those topics up. however, that small detail is the only thing id tweek. üòã

I downloaded this app because I thought the logo was cute and now I really like it. I find myself actually looking forward to the messages I get, since their arrival is delayed according to how far away the sender is. It's a nice compromise between instant messaging and actually sending a letter in the mail. I just wish I could search for people based on language proficiency, or at least filter out people who only have a language marked as "Interested." I use the app to find Japanese language speakers, and finding people who are "interested" in Japanese, along with 4 or 5 other languages, is not helpful.
Really interesting little app. Just wish i was a bit quicker at typing with my thumbs! Still enjoying, and the web version is great, although log in a bit clunky. Still 5*.

This app has changed the way to communicate with others around the world. I have messaged two pen pals so far that live in Europe. The app makes it easy to send a letter, and builds the suspense throught the real time letter transaction (which makes this app more unique than other apps). However, I would fine tune the age range seeing as I often chatting 25 year olds when I set my range 10-20. Other than that, this app is great.

It's wonderful. Usually there are a bunch of weirdos on apps like this but, not here. There are SO many people and they're definitely not disappointing. The concept is also very real from a pen pal POV. The letter gets delivered based on how far it is. To people living close, it takes 1 hour or so. Far away people, can get it delivered as slowly as 1 day or more. Brings out the real feel of sending actually letters across the globe.
Whenever I'm typing longer letters, in tends to lag alot. This i only experienced in the mobile version of the app though. Wether it's my phone or the app, I hope they can improve this soon...

What a lovely idea! I really enjoy the fact that you choose between various preset profile pictures/icons for your profile, instead of your own photos. Weirdly/not so weirdly it allows the focus to be on the persons other details (bio, interests, languages spoken, country of residence etc) . In a world where everything is instant and potential connections are so plentiful that they almost lose value, or at least for me result in choice paralysis or a constant engagement in short superficial interactions, I really appreciate the time it takes for your letter to be received. You have something to look forward to. In turn, you put time into the quality and depth of your response, knowing that it will take just as long to return, and so that it will be like they say "worth their wait". A wonderful app to have sincere thought out conversations with people around the world. Thank you developers (:

Hi there i really like the construction of this app. This app this working now!! with no errors. I should say thanks because we are living in a smart generation but you are all thinnking in a vintage generation. This idea is very great. I really like this app. But I have left one more star because, I think this app does not gives much privacy and security to the users. So please try to add end- to end encryption to maintain more security to the users

I love the idea of this apps, modern version of letter! Back to the good old times! I enjoyed receiving new letters from my penpals here! and i didnt know that I love to write until I wrote tons of letter here ü§™ Thankyouuu

this app is amazing. the concept of writing letters on the phone and sending it to someone on the world is briliiant. The funny thing is that you get responses days after you wrote something and that is very up cheering, because you don't expect a response (that fast). The app is also improving your focus because, you do something and don't get an instant gradification, so you do something for yourself in a later moment.

Why did you remove the filter to see people who have been online in the last 24 hours?! There are countless of inactive users on the search results. That was the most useful filter that you removed it! ü§¶üèª

When I heard about this app, and the concept behind it, I was rather intrigued, for it isn't often that one finds a service that prides itself on performing a task slower than its competitors. However, this app has struck gold with this idea, since people put in far greater effort into crafting their letters than what is common on similar penpal apps. The animated profile pictures, unrestricted word count, and the simple, minimalistic, user-friendly interface only serve to make it more endearing.

I love this app sm but here are some suggestions for improvement! 1. Many people disappear after exchanging a couple of letters. It would be great if it's possible to line up the search result according how reactive he/she has been. 2. There are people who share many common interests and some just share a few. I also want a filter or line up fuction so I can find people with similar interests easily. 3. Many people aren't aware of different stamps so please add a tutorial so I can collect them
The only problem I have with this app is that when we write massive letters it lags although I have a galaxy A50 (6,64). Hope the team fix this soon. Best wishes.
This app is very cool. I like the concept and it is a bit exciting receiving a letter, feels different than a common message on any other app..you guys should give it a go it's fun :)

SLOWLY is the best app I've come across in a long time. I always wanted a pen pal when I was younger, but was never brave enough to reach out to one. Slowly matches and initiates you with people so smoothly that I have met great people, and had cool things to talk about without being anxious at all. I think my favorite feature is that the letter takes as long to get to each place as they would in regular mail, so it is completely different than instant messaging. It saves the charm of much loved pastime. So far, great experience! Thank you developers for an amazing app! If you would like to meet new people across the world and make new friends, I'd definitely recommend installing SLOWLY.
I've had this app for a few months now and it's the best. it makes sure to confirm before you send a letter, saves drafts and let's you talk to people who like similar things as you.

I really like this app BUT!! I've been having a serious bug problem that needs to be fixed. For about a week now, I can't interact with anything in the app besides the four icons at the bottom of the screen (home, letters, ongoing letters, profile). Nothing else-- I can't search for new matches, I can't open letters,I can't open drafts or respond, u can't even interact with anything on my profile. PLEASE FIX!!!

I enjoy using this app to connect with people from around the world. I miss the old ways of sending mails, but that comes at a expensive time/price. This mimics that part of life back then when you want to send a snail mail to someone. I love that concept- I believe it's more intimate and makes you appreciate it more. Thank you for doing this, Why Interactive!

One of my favorite social apps on the app market right now.  Waiting for letters to send due to Geolocation is a really neat idea that makes the app thrilling to use.  It also ensures that both you and the person you're conversing with are more likely to put some real effort into the letter, because no one wants to wait 2 days for a letter that is clearly not interesting.  Devs are also very responsive - even to feedback.    I've made some cool friends already through this app, and have many more to make.  All the while, 0 microtransactions and 0 ads.  This is how you make an app.  Thanks so much, Slowly devs!

This app is something I never knew i needed in my life. With how instant everything is nowadays, it's a refreshing change of pace. I've only been using it for less than a day and have had some extremely interesting and insightful conversations, meeting some great people who share my interests. My small issues are about avatars, and genders. (Oh no! A SJW! They cry.) I personally am very uncomfortable with people being able to target me for what sex I was born as (I am non-binary and would not like to be labelled as my birth sex, yes, but that isn't the only reason for this.) Even without that issue, the avatar choice seems a little lacking. Otherwise, a very good app I would recommend to anybody. Works smoothly, concept and execution is wonderful!

I like the concept of the app ! Meeting new poeple who shares the same interest with you, interact with them and also having to wait for the letter to deliver, it's like sending a real letter to people !

Perfect app to find pen pals, and actually writing worth to wait messages. Some people think that it takes too much time to receive and send messages, but the maximun time I have seen is one day. The point of this is being patient (and excited!) for the replies, which is something that will make people give up on the app, unfortunately.
Slowly makes you learn about relationships that need to be taken slowly. You can't rush into it! üòâ
I loved the experience within the app. I liked the concept of the app, nice and private, and option to connect from around the world! Five stars!

i liked it. only 2 days into it. found no bots thankfully. but did find rude people, of course they are part and parcel of the game. it's a good thought by the app developers. thank you for taking the Letters day and night and not waiting like the actual post office which opens only the next day morning. hopefully I'll find more stories to listen and share here.

it's always an interesting social app to make friends who do appreciate the beauty of letter-writting. The stamp system also added a touch of card collecting game to the whole thing. i am a bit disappointed when they started to sell stamps in the stamp store, it obviously lost the fun of collecting letters from friends all over the world and now it to some extent become to me another pay-to-exceed game.

Very good for what it is. However, I have run into a few bugs, but nothing major. For example sometimes when I open the app I cannot open letters but I can switch tabs. I wish it was possible to get a coin for every so many letters you send too so that way it could be possible to eventually buy new stamps without spending money. That said I understand what they are going for with their monetization strategy, and it's not bad at all. I also wish letters took longer to arrive/send.

Awesome app in the age of instant satisfaction. Practical design with no forced ad or payment. Great graphic design. The community of users right now are respectful and diverse. Hope it stays the same in the future. One note for users, I find the usage of pining late. It is designed to read the previous letter while you are writing a new one.
This is a very good app, firstly to improve writing skills as far as I'm comcerned. I'm yet to find how to talk to people for a long time. More stamps would be better. Thank you.

I've really enjoyed this app. I've enjoyed conversations and penpals for years but what makes this app great is that it combines the cheap, easy and accessible benefits of technology and the internet without having the downside, at least to me, of instant communication. the only knock against the app that i have is that some users are attempting to beg for money instead of just wanting to communicate in good faith.

I'm really enjoying the app so far. The only bad thing is starting off it's a little slow, because you have to wait for your letters to send and hope someone writes back. But that's not the apps fault. (in fact you could argue it's one of it's charm's) I know a lot of people don't like the long wait times between letters, but to me it adds to the experience. It's so exciting to see a letter coming from halfway around the world and I find myself watching the time, counting down the hours till my next one arrives. If you want to meet new people, but don't like the boring not so personal interactions that come from most instant messaging (at least that's my most common experience with people I've met online) this is a great alternative. Plus you never have to work around one another's schedule/ time zones.

I really really loved this app but since yesterday it won't start. It just stays on the loading page. So I decided to reinstall it but it still does the same. Now I'm afraid I've lost all my data because I reinstalled it and the app won't even start. I'd love if it could work again, because now I can't talk to some of the friends I've made. Edit: It's working now, I hope it doesn't happen again! Apart from that it's a really nice app and I recommend it!
Not too much to say about it. UI is simple and very well designed, it does everything it claims to do. A very good throwback to a relatively lost hobby.

I love this app! There's something special about sending long, thought out messages to people and the anticipation of their reply which makes connections so much more special. I'm chatting to people on the other side of the world and I feel like I'm forming quite a strong connection with some of them, despite the wait, or perhaps because of it. As I write this, I'm filled with anticipation, because a letter from the person I've talked to most will be arriving in a few hours, and I've been looking forward to it for almost two days now. I feel like I've really made quite a strong connection with this person, and yet I never would have talked to them if not for SLOWLY. It's so well designed, I love the simple layout, the multitude of options for interests, the matching, everything. Being able to filter through potential friends based on many different characteristics is super helpful for finding people to talk to. The anonymity of an avatar for the profile picture and using a nickname is great. The support staff are very quick to respond to any issues
Really easy to use, fun app. Gets you talking to people around the world in a much more meaningful way than most other instant social networking apps. Love it!

This app is incredible. I am SO happy I found it. This is much more satisfying than meeting people on more "shallow" chat apps. I've made lots of interesting friends!!! I love the control you have to set your interests and find people with similar ones. I love the stamp collecting (devs, more stamps for more things please please üôè). The photo sharing request and accept process could be improved and less hidden deep in the settings. I would expect to simply tap the camera icon in my letter draft to request photo sharing. I LOVE the graphic design of the app. I love the time it takes to mail letters!

This app is just great! I've been looking for a concept like this for a long time. Developers: you've done a great job with this app! One thing is missing, and that's why the four stars: read and write offline. If I only could read letters that already came to my phone when I was online, and also reply to them, and it will to be sent when I came online again, this app would be perfect. Another nice-to-have would be dark mode. Thank you developers!

Absolutely love this concept! I downloaded and installed this app in the morning on a whim. The whole idea of waiting in anticipation for your letter to arrive is fantastic. I created my profile and started looking around. I've already written to two people from Japan and Northeast India. I can see that they've replied and their messages will arrive in 18 and 3 hours respectively. Just like an actual snail mail!!. The app layout is clean and simple. I have several dating messaging apps and I personally think this far better. It's good to get away from instant gratification for a change. I highly like and recommend this app!

To make it as short as possible (not as long as the letters I'm writing), this app is great! I was able to meet lots of amazing perople form all around the world that allowed me to take a peek into their culture and grasp their opinions about the world. Endless conversations and debates were possible thanks to this app, so you've done a great job!

I really enjoy the concept. I enjoy traveling, but not always able to travel, so it is quite nice to talk to people around the world. I enjoy that it feels more like real time because it takes time for the letters to be sent & received. But I thoroughly enjoy just being able to talk to people about any topic with an open mind & no strings attached. I wish there were some ways to personalize my profile, but I am enjoying my world wide experience. Peace Shalom

One of the best social media apps. Takes you away from instant messaging and really taking genuinity into the messages. In order to make up for the waiting time, you need to write longer messages, which I think brings out the personality of each person. Highly recommended! But I hope you could reduce the current waiting time by around 10-15%. I'm have pals from the same country yet some take me 2-3h to wait.

This is a really interesting app and definitely so cool with the penpal and slow delivery. Brings back tge traditional penpal. I really like it and think its found its own niche in the social media space.

Okay, this is a really nice app. I'm someone who loves writing and making friends digitally (don't we all suck at IRL socialisation?) and Slowly offers me the chance to do both at the same time. I don't really have suggestions for improvement, either. It's just really cool overall. Keep up the great work! :)
It is a great application for anyone who loves writing long letters. It really takes long to receive and send letters which takes you to old times in a good way.

I love this app. It is phenomenal. I have met an abundance of people with different backgrounds. The UI is clean-cut and fresh, I love the fact that Slowly places emphasis on the connecting part of the experience and not on photos. Even though it takes a while for the letters to send based on location, its usually worth the wait. Honestly, the waiting won't be much of a problem when you have a lot of people writing to you. Thank for this app, it is a God send.

I am using this app a lot and enjoying it. You can connect to lot of interesting people. It would benefit from enhancements such as being able to search for specific people or to note people you might want to contact later. Also there seem to be many people listed who have not been on for months. But overall it is a lot of fun. I have donated some money to keep it going.

A great experience for anyone who wants to send letters the old fashioned way. Especially great with stamp collecting. The hard part is keeping yourself patient, but that's our own fault. I wish we had more stamps to trade around, but it's not an issue. Maybe if we have more options for customizing letters by using signatures or paper colors or even designs on the paper itself. Maybe even choose what kind of font for those who really want to feel like an individual

This app let you interact with people around the world. Whether random or with specific like which country, common language that you know, or someone with same interest. It's really is great. Thank you very much Dev. people, and I am also waiting for future update. Maybe there will be more feature to search for people, like distance(around user) or more.

At first this app was great, I used to spend all my free time reading and writing letters. But after one of the updates (I guess) it kinda stopped working. It constantly asks for my location. I get the point but I don't think it should be compulsory every time I open the app. Moreover, after I agree to share location, the app starts loading messages and it just never ends. This makes the app impossible to use! Is there a way to fix this? I really miss this app :( EDIT: When I tried opening the app just now, it worked perfectly. Still, most of the time it never stops loading. What might be the cause of this?

i reallyyyy like this app, it gives you many optional interests to match with people, and i also really like the filters to look for specific genders, locations, or topics.. it also has a nonbinary option, and doesnt limit your character options no matter what gender you choose i also really like how there seems to be no limit on how much you can write in your bio or letters (i write long letters and havent met any limit yet)

It's a great idea, and up until now that idea worked for me. What i have a problem with is the software. The app always takes to minutes on startup, during which it's basically not responding. After that it works fluent most of the time, but sometimes it randomly decides to get super laggy for a moment. Not to forget that it crashed once and almost bricked my phone.

It's fantastic that it's add free. It's beautifully made too. I really like the concept behind it. I don't really get the stamps thing yet, it would be nice to be able to design and use your own stamps. I think if you get a lot of pen pals might be tricky to see who you need to write back to (maybe that's because I'm not used to it yet). Fantastic thou, well recommended!

I love this app so much! I love connecting with other people around the world and the community is so nice. The app is easy to navigate. My only complaints are I wish the avatar could have more to choose from (there was no blonde hair or hair of a lot of diff colors and the skin tones were strange too.) I also wish the app allowed you to add interests/hobbies, for example I wish I could add fencing. But these don't make it a worse app but if they added it it would be awesome

I've been having great fun sending letters, and watching replies fly their way towards me. It's odd in the world we live in to know that a letter is in transit and there's no possible way someone could have read it yet. I find I like it, having an immediate response to an email always felt overwhelming, as if someone expects you to make a decision there and then. With slowly you can take your time and think about what you want to say without feeling the pressure to answer immediately as even if you do send a response moments after receiving a letter, you know it's not going to be there for hours! It's good, takes a lot of my anxiety about letters and pen friends away.
Very authentic experience if you really into writing letters and can find some people echoing your thoughts. But after a while, the application starts to lag. Need fixation.

Great app, could easily be a 5 star review but there are two things that are annoying to me. The first is that the letter take far to long to send. I get that it is not supposed to be a generic social media app, but since in currently live in Canada, it takes an entire day to communicate with my pen pals from Russia and Ukraine. One day is a little too long, don't you think? The second minor flaw is that I can't use this app in split screen view because every time I tap back, i restarts.

So far I'm really liking this app. I have actual snail mail penpals and I've always thought that the slowness helps people connect better than instant messaging. This app allows that slowness to happen easier and with less effort & money. So far, my only qualm is that the sent/recieved ratio tends to revert back to 1:1. Sometimes if I restart the app, it'll go back to normal. The ratio is also slow to update or just not correct. Example: My ratio was 3:2 even though I had received 3, not 2.

This app has a very unique charm and style. I also like completing my stamp collection. But there are some things that put me off. I've been on the app for more than a year, and most of the letters I get are from men asking me for my private info, or flirting with me. To the point I had to specify in my profile that I'm not interested in those kind of letters. And still they arrive. Plus, the web version is badly optimized.

This app is brilliant. Not only does it give you the chance to talk to other people all over the world like other similar apps it has one unique quality that makes it stand out. It forces the user to wait for a response. So often since the advent of Cellular technology we find ourselves demanding instant availability and instant gratification. This app steps outside of that expectation and asks us to wait. This was an absolute risk the developer was taking and I hope it turns out to have been worthwhile. It's healthy for us to slow down and wait for something. It adds value just being forced to wait. There are a lot of subtle psychological benefits to be had in using an app like this. Kudos to the developers on being so bold as to create an app asking us to be patient. Five stars

I must say that the UI is spot-on. The app is extremely easy to use. However, I have been trying to send a letter for quite sometime now. The page keeps loading and doesn't respond. Some fields like personal description, friend-finder, among others keep loading until you get tired of waiting. It'd be wonderful if you could address these issues.

I really love the idea behind the app and the design is lovely. The one downside which has a big impact on the overall experience is the bad filtering and searching for matching profiles. The search is very basic and searching for a a good matching pen pal is difficult. This means it takes long time to get a good conversation started. Improved search and auto matching would make it the best app.
It's a wonderful app to build International relations with! Although it requires patience - especially when the receiver lives in a long distances. But this app totally deserves 5 stars.

Hi, I recently got the app and love it so much but I'm having a few troubles. The app stays in the gray loading screen and doesn't load up the app and whenever I try to see messages it won't let me. Please give the app a update so we may all enjoy it! I really wanna make new friends and send out letters. I love the concept of this app and it's so much fun, please please pleaaaase update it!

The app is fantastic. People complaining about the time it takes to deliver and receive letters do not understand the purpouse of the app. The design is beautiful. There are no annoying ads, and the map feature makes it feel like old school mailing which makes the waiting a little bit more bearable. Also, no micro transactions other than to buy stamps which might be worth it if you're into it.

I love it, in the beginning i was unsre how to begin sending letters to others, but i SLOWLY got the hang of it. And once you get a response from someone, it is the most exciting feeling in the world. The interest matching is a great tool to use to get to know other people, and the bios are so fun to read. Totally worth the wait and time to write letters
It's a beautiful concept and the UI is pretty easy; one less star since there's no option for finding people under the tags of Yoga, Meditation, Spirituality, etc.

I really like this app but I find the age settings really inconvenient. I'd like to talk to people around my age (18-19) but the filter only allows for you to filter people in 5s. There is a huge difference between 15 and 20 year olds and I don't feel comfortable talking to strangers younger than 17 online. Please, can you make the age filters more specific?

I'm liking this app because it takes the rush out of a thing. Like when you get to know a new person and you both text constantly and rush into it and then get bored. It's not like that, it sends the letters in a more realistic way, and that's very cool. Also the thing about common topics is cool, like before sending a letter you can see what common topics you both have and you can start a coversation based on it. So far loving the app.

Still getting used to the app. But I really like the concept of SLOWLY. Especially the possibility that messages take a day or two to reach is at the same time both relaxing and exciting. The anticipation for news, letters, postcards; it's something we have almost forgotten to appreciate. Through SLOWLY, the idea of letters embraces us back like a long lost sibling, and we begin to appreciate the beauty of anticipating something again.

There are ways around this issue, but I do wish this was not just an app but also workable on the desktop, since typing on a phone is such a pesky task.  I have only just downloaded this so no opinion yet on how it works. I must say that the lack of desktop options almost stopped me from trying though. I think the idea sounds great though. So, we will see...

Its a brilliant way to pen pall, and make friends! Also a more eco friendly way of doing it by having it all digital keeps paper wastage down, plus safer. Well worth the download! Though I'd like to see more detailed bio options other than the currant tags, though more tag options would also be sweet! It be good to see more info on a potential pen pall, responce rate and likleyness, how long they've been using Slowy, ect.

It's a great app for someone who likes meaningful conversations. And also for someone like me who hates chatting for long hours. üòÇ This gives me time to breathe and come up with a thoughtful reply.

I was skeptical at first (c'mon, digital pen pals?? O_o). However, after giving it an honest try, I'm now a convert! The quality of correspondence you can get out of this app is on another level compared to every single other social app I've tried. The more effort you put into it, the more enjoyment you will reap.

So, i love this app and i really love the concept. There is nothing bad i can say about the general idea but i cant give it 5 stars cose the app doesnt work properly. Sometimes it doesn't send the letter, instead just stays there trying and it freezes. Also, scrolling is sometimes very laggy, and navigating through the app bugged sometimes. This is a nice thoughtful app. I enjoy the process of communicating with new friends via writing the long letters at my own time. The app create another chance of 'me' time for me.

Besides minor bugs like session kicking me out all the time or app getting frozen now and then, I think that the work done on this app is amazing. I loved the concept from day one and I'm pretty sure the app will continue to evolve. I personally would like to congratulate the developers and the time invested so far. Thank you for making this possible, connecting people from different backgrounds and cultures without selling ads or data is just amazing.

Out of the apps I installed which are about making friends with peope outside my country, this is the best and this app really exceeds my expectations. I felt happy for people I became friends with this application. Although it takes a while to receive their letters and send mine, still it makes me eager to hear from them. This app really tests your patience and this makes the friendship built become more meaningful. Thank you developers and to all the people behind the success of this app!
It's wonderful. I've met a lot of amazing people on here and the concept of exchanging letters is such a vintage and cool idea. Literally get this if you're looking to find pen pals

I love this app. The concept with realistic arrival times of the letters makes it sometimes a bit annoying but actually makes sense, firstly because of the overall letter concept and secondly because it makes the arrival of the letters even more exciting. Definitely recommending this if you want to meet people with similar interests around the globe.

Love it! My biggest gripe with other messaging apps is that you quickly lose interest in the people you meet along the way. By nature the pacing in the app makes it so that you don't burn out, and pushes you to make seriously thought out messages. Highly recommended to people who want to try and make meaningful connections in an interesting way.

Great concept in fast paced era, I am writing this after installing the app about 2-3 hours ago. app UI doesn't have anything to complain about and it kind of explain itself clearly. Saw it pop up as a suggested app and I've been in love with it since I installed it. I have been meaning to look for something like this for a very long time and I can say, I have found it. This review will change with further use as it's still just the first week. That being said, I've made a dozen friends already :) One issue I have noticed is that on smaller phones with lower resolutions, some menus are not being displayed correctly. For example, on my Freetel FTJ16A, I am unable to see the explore manually button in the 'Ready to meet a new pal' window when the Auto Match button is present. It displays fine on my Galaxy S7 edge however so this may be a programming issue. That aside, everything works great! Keep up the good work!

A really good app, it's truly slow. However that is what the app is for. So has no problem. I would like to add new topics, more variety would be really good.

I love SLOWLY and all. I loved this app, but I just went to go to my account after being away for a couple of days and my account has randomly been deleted

this app is good! maybe in this digital era which everything is easy and fast, to wait for our letter pass to someone in a day or 2 day and wait for someone to replying our letter and its also deliver to us in a day is little bit boring. Slowly is an amazing app that allows you to get in contact with people around the world via digital postcards. The time you receive the card depends on the distance you are from the sender, and the delayed gratification makes you think about what you write. Waiting almost makes the message even more meaningful. The app us very user-friendly, and it's available in almost, if not all languages. Would recommend to anyone who wants to find friends around the world.

Yes. I'm really looking the concept of this app. I've always wanted a penpal to write to, and the surprise and anticipation of getting a reply. I actually wouldn't mind having the option/check box/settings of having 1) not knowing if the letter is coming (nor the length of time for arrival), and 2) having a more realistic/longer snail mail length of time. Not hours, but days, or a week+, just like real life.

MY PHONE HANGS ALL THE TIME SINCE USING THIS APP, WHILE I REMOVED IT, FORMATTED MY PHONE RE INSTALLED *Slowly* but my phone continues to work super slowly and hangs due to this app. The app was a very good one if the hanging thing was not a problem.

I like the concept, and so far; all good, I wish you could have a little more specificity when it comes to your location, like city or something; feel like that would make it more interesting if you find someone in your own country. (don't know if the usa has states or something, but you could do the same with regions in other countries, if cities is too specific that is). I honestly wouldn't mind it either if the travel time for letters was a bit longer, but that might of course just be me, the fun side of that would of course be that if you go on a vacation somewhere closer to your pen pal, it would have more of a real impact on the waiting time. but again, I don't know if this is something that appeals to everyone of course. good luck onwards, hope you find joy in keeping the app going.

Great idea and well executed. Be interesting to see if people maintain momentum. Couple of suggestions: firstly either more topics for interests or the ability to define your own. Secondly, I don't know if it's just me, but i feel the need to respond immediately so the other person doesn't feel like they're being ignored so the ability to snooze a response might help

I was able to communicate with other people easier and safer. Its not as demanding as other messaging apps and it doesn't show location of where I am in my country. Must try for some introverted people!

I've only joined 2 days ago but I absolutely recommend this app for those who are looking for sincere penpals. The beauty of this app is being penpals with people from all over the world without going through the hassle of sending it via post office. It takes different durations to send/receive a letter depending on the country of your penpal but it just makes you more excited to receive/send one. I'm quite new to this app but I have already found 4 very nice people. GIVE IT A TRY!!

I had to shut it off, which means I can't use it to look, either. If not for the few actual connections I have made, I probably would have deleted the app a couple of weeks ago.

I love this app - love the use of avatars instead of pictures, love the low pressure slow responses, love the vibes - every message so far has been positive and lovely. Happily chatting to people all over the world. The delay in messages makes for more fun & anticipation. Would love the age by year (or at least over 18 clear cutoff) & the topics to be a bit more specific (MeetUp is a great example of an app with really granular interests). Stamp suggestions - Chinese year animals, age stamps.

One of a kind app. Special thanks to the team for introducing the pen friend experience in our digital type. While whole world is getting rotten by instant message services, the anticipation of getting a letter digitally is like breathing fresh air. Also I greatly appreciate the team of SLOWLY to keep this app ad-free. Thank you so much. Love from India & Philippines.
Good concept, App need some fixes though. Issue im facing: App does not go beyond white login screen most of the time. If you can fix this issue for me then great, Ill give you 5 stars.
Love the app! Great idea and great execution! The only criticism I could offer would be an achievement list to know how many achievement-stamps you can collect!

I love this app!! I never feel more connecting with the world than now. Its a perfect combination between modern tech and old letter. Great app to meet new friends. It's refreshing to have a delay in messages being sent and received, very different to other platforms. I'd recommend it.

I just started using this app, and already love it. It's easy to set up and start searching for people to write to. I used to have pen pals when I was a kid, and loved getting letters in the mail. Glad I found this app! Definitely a keeper!

I love this app! It's been so fun getting to know people around the world, and it's a great way to practice a second language. The time delay is a plus, I don't feel pressure to respond immediately like I would in instant messaging, and knowing you have a letter from a pal arriving is fun anticipation. The interface is easy to use and nice to look at without being too busy.

It's a very good concept, it takes a long time to receive letters, but because of the wait it is something special! Something i really enjoy as well is the fact, that you get longer letters, not just "Hey, How are you" type of messages. I haven't experienced any problems with this app so far, so i have no reason to give a worse rating than i did.

unlike most other apps, the people you "meet" are generally well meaning and appropriate. you can talk about things that maybe others aren't usually interested in. The app is great I have met some really nice people and just hoping to have long lasting relationships

This is the best messanging apps that Ive ever used so far. You could share your interests with the others and feel the energize of waiting the messages like the old time. Befriend with anyone never been this excitement.

For the past few days that I've been using this app, I absolutely love it! I also really like the idea and concept of this app, and I even think that the execution was done pretty well. There have been a few crashes here and there, but that hasn't affected my overall experience that much. A fun idea that would be cool is to be able to use a variety of stamps instead of just a select few, or be able to customize a letter with small stickers or decorations, but they don't need to add those features. What would be useful is if the organizing aspect of the friends list was tweaked up a bit. Instead of a list, it would be nice to have an overview of the friends and letters that you've sent instead of having just one list full of names. I've gotten a ton of letters in the past few days and it's a bit of a hassle sorting through one list by scrolling to the side. It would be nice to have a separate list of letters so that I can keep track of what I've received, what I've sent and what I haven't replied to yet.

It's a really very fun and unique concept. Waiting for letters to reach my country (Pakistan) from the Americas though is an exercise in extreme patience...2 days on average. The best part is that you can filter out who gets to send you letters which is a VERY handy feature if you're a woman because men on the Internet can be an overenthusiastic horde sometimes. It also lets you pick your gender as non-binary which is more than can be said of other apps. Looking at you, Pen Pals. No profile pics.

The app itself is a great concept and I adore it. Although your experience depends on who you write to/recieve letters from, most people on this app are friendly and nice. Throughly enjoying this app. Great quality of conversations. It is refreshing to wait in anticipation for a letter. I love this app and I think I will know more great people out there to pour my heart out to. Wonderful and elegant. Distance and the wait make me cherish what I have now. I love you guys! Fighting!

As an application this is perfect with perfect concept of an app. But user base is lame. Sometimes you write those long letters and people don't even revert so I guess it's better to put all that effort where it's fruitful

Seriously one of my favorite apps. I have met so many amazing people and have been able to connect in new ways. I LOVE this app. I used to have snail mail penpals and this is the best digital equivalent I have found. I've rarely rated apps when they asked me about it, but I feel like I can make an exception for Slowly. I've used the app since September of 2018 and am still actively using it to talk to people. I've met loads of amazing people over the year, and it's not gonna stop. It might be overwhelming at times, which is maybe my only gripe with the app.

I like the app it's a smart way to communicate with people but I have a slight problem. When I go on to type a letter my keyboard and phone over all slows down. Idk, I love sending postcards all around the world irl, but not for the reasons this app features. This is the perfect app for any introvert that seeks to find a few pen pals. Very interesting concept. App runs smoothly and works exactly as advertised. Personally, I dislike writing on mobile: long-form double so. Nice idea. App itself works perfectly & without issues. Design is really nice and modern too. I love this app! Easily matched penpals from all around the world. Mails take time to deliver really gives the feeling of posting a real mail, and I already have new friends that I love! Oh Jesus thank you dear developer for making this

it's a lovely app! i've become connected with quite a few people who are very friendly. it would be nice if the app added a translation system for those who are not good at speaking languages different from their native tongue. this isn't a problem with me since most of the people i get seem to speak somewhat english, but i can tell it's hard for them since it's not their first language. overall, a wonderful app that can create friendships instantly.

Whatsapp and LINE Killer! In an instant era, I need something to slower my pace and this app offer the best. Just keep the app features like this, all seems perfect, adding avatars and poststamps for xtra spices.

I love this app! I have no issues whatsoever. It does what the description says and its such a beautiful experience connecting with strangers from around the world

I hesitated at first to download this app but I finally took the leap and boy has it been reviving the embers of my love for writing paragraphs. It is like the others said, anticipation of a letter arriving makes it more cherished. The design of this app is very aesthetic, modern, and cheerful, and the iconography visuals are pleasing to the eye, but also easy to get a hang of. So far a great experience.

Slowly is very easy to use with cute graphics and lots of information and things that help you know what's going on, like who is sending to you, how long it will take for you to finally receive the letter, and even when your penpals were last online (if they enable it). The only thing I think they should add is a pause on incoming letters to stop people from sending letters to you if you feel like you're being overwhelmed at least temporarily.

I like this app more than I thought I would. I thought it would be full of trolls and unsolicited sexual content but it's not. I've had some really genuine conversations. It feels the same as having a physical pen pal. Opening the app sometimes glitches for a few seconds but I expect that will be fixed soon. Highly recommend if you want real human interactions.

It's a good way to meet and make new friends. And it's exciting to see that there's letter arriving. And fun to see also that my letter will arrive to my friend in a couple of hours or even days. Really like a snail mail. Just like the old days. üòÅ

Slowly is an amazing concept and I am very happy I came across this app. You get to have a penpal without giving out your address, it's completely online and I love the fact it's not an instant message. The farther away the person lives from you the longer your letter takes to get them. I have no complaints and I've met a couple interesting people so far. I have and will suggest Slowly to people.

Very nice app. i have been using every since it came out and its fun to talk to people with this. i have trouble making friends in real life and with this is easy to talk to people with the same age range, gender and interestd. be cool if while you were searching for someone to talk to if you could pick topics you dont wants

I am so glad I downloaded this app. It's great for making new friends, learning about other cultures and languages, and you can have some really great discussions. The only thing I'm not a fan of is that when you get a letter, if you have the setting of receiving new friends on, if you dont reply it sends your ratios off. Sometimes you just dont think there is anything worth while to talk about. Otherwise, I truly appreciate this app.

As many other interested users who downloaded this app, I got the "System Error" message when creating my account. Unfortunately, the dev team does not seem to be addressing these issues, even on their home page, where a help/support search yields no results for troubleshooting. There are also no responses from the dev team on these reviews, which is irresponsible, considering how many have had this issue.

I was going to give 5 star review until suddenly stop working. "JSON Parse Error: Unrecognized token ">"" and "System error" keeps popping out and it wouldnt let log into my account, either that or it freezes at the loading screen . I can't seem to make it work even after reinstalling the app. I really do enjoy using this app... Please do something to fix this.
I wish this was a bit more direct. I like the pen pal nature and that it takes real time to get messages across, but I also wish there was a way to cut out the wait when you want.

I was very sceptical about the app, but it works as intended. Easy to use and find people to chat with. Letters take time to arrive, so you have to wait, sometimes even a day :) It is creating a brilliant feeling of excitement. I had no issues whatsoever. 5 stars from me, well done devs!

The app is great, kudos to the team!..clean design, nice stamps easy to use. The only downside.. I was excited n the beginning, but too many people loose interest and just quit. People who plan to download this..please understand that writing letters takes time..probably half to 1 hour. Please download the app only if you have that kind of time to spare..oh, and have the basic courtesy to inform when you decide to quit the app instead of vanishing off.

This is my only issue with it, it's quite simple and otherwise works. It doesn't really relay the excitement of getting real mail though, maybe adding some more script like font choices would help with that.

Awesome app, really helps connecting people in a very good way. Haven't found anything bad with it at all! Recommended for everyone who wants to connect to people all over the world. You cant go wrong with it! Special thanks to developers for replying/helping very fast and even making new stamps in a matter of days after requested!
What a nice concept on this modern age! Combining current technology and the intimacy of a snail mails to create this wonderful app. Highly recommended if you want meaningful connections.

I really like this app. I never thought that about a pen pal experience will be something nowdays, but here it is. I got to meet new actual friends from far away lands and share our lives with each other. The app still need more features, but the developers are improving it slowly (pun intended).
I enjoy this app. However, I am experiencing an annoying problem: everytime I leave the app, it logs me out! Idk why, but it's getting to be annoying. Please fix it :/

I personally love this app. I've always wanted to send letters to someone but I never really had anyone that wanted to do it since we can just text. I've encountered no issues up to this point, they did a great job at making the app.
Truly amazing app, I have been using it for couple months now, if there was some way to back up letters to computer it would be even better!

The app deserves nothing less than 5 stars, but 3 stars because of the updated Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. They take permission to share everything with third parties for commercial purposes, and continue to do so even after the account is deleted. It was good fun but sadly, I may have a to delete it now.

The idea and concept is there. I do not mind the long waiting time. It makes me excited to receive letters. Maybe it can be addressed by adding more features.. i dont really know what it is to make it more fun and interesting... also maybe updating the topics I guess...

I really, really love this app. It is hands down one of the best apps I've ever downloaded. The premise of the app is clever, the art is cute, the execution is well done. But otherwise, this app is adorable and I love it!

Pretty cool! Sadly it does take quite a while for receive the msg but it's the whole point. We are so used to instant stuff. But this is cool!

I usually don't take the time to review apps but this app is a gem. anyone with a smartphone should download it. I am very glad I downloaded it. the point of the app is essentially virtual snail mail. the app is not for instant messaging, which is what's nice about it. it's a good tool to practice writing skills and connect with people. and it's always exciting to receive a new letter. 10outof10 would recommend

Overall, the concept is wonderful! I've learned so much just by talking to people in other countries who also thought the concept was neat. I have a few gripes, mainly in how you can't search for specific friends who may live elsewhere that you want to send letters to.there's a few other annoyances but overall it's wonderful!

Works exactly like it says. What you get out of it depends on what you put in. You might not match with a compatible penpal for a while, which isn't something the app is missing; it's just a numbers game. I actually thought it would take longer to send and receive messages. It seems to work as if the letter goes straight on a plane when you press the send button, instead of taking into account the time spent in a post box or at the post office. A penpal is still a penpal though.

Love the app! However I wish there was a "Mark as unread" option available. I prefer taking time to reply to a letter, however can't repress my curiosity and open the letter anyway. And I happen to do this will all messages and after a while I forget what letters u haven't replied to! This is a really fun app. i had many pen pals as a child so I love the idea! I'd highly recommend that the devs create a toggle which indicates whether someone is single to prevent this kind of misunderstanding. I've had to add details of my private life to my profile to avoid being romanced.

It's fun to be forced to write a bit longer messages because it takes some time before it arrives. Been using this app for a couple weeks now and so far I have been enjoying it a lot. This is a pretty cool app if you want to find a penpal that lives somewhere else in the world. The concept is interesting enough. I've been using it for some days now AND I LOVE IT! Slowly is quite a unique and pretty cool experience, no "likes" or ads type of app. I love that it takes actual time for letter to travel and arrive to my pen pal, and no pressure to immediately reply. Since I started using Slowly my pen pals have been nice and interesting people from all over the world. For people like me who are curious and like to write, learn and share ideas with others, this is the app.

Very cool concept and well achieved! There are so many locations and languages. If you have a hard time meeting new people, this app is for you. Not only do you get to acquire new friends that you may have difficulties making in person, but you also get to learn about a different culture first hand as well as improve your conversation skills. Well, honestly, I loved this app when I first got it. It's a really good idea for people that love technology but also want to go back to the days of writing letters and having pen pals. Kind of hard to write letters to pen pals, or even to have a pen pal, when they are not writing back. I'm starting to lose interest in this app.

This app really stands out as a concept in the ephemeral world of instant online communication. During automatch, it would be nice to be able to look at the profiles of your matches before sending the message. Great experience! It's like any other app to message random people around the world but more wholesome! I love the UI .. it's simple and beautiful... and also, I love how this apps works, especially when I can collect stamps all over the world and having pen-pals without really knowing how do they look like (yes I think the digital avatars are better than real life pics) so we can focus more on what they write rather than how they look like.

Really amazing app. Waiting for the letters to arrive reminds me of the excitement and joy of my childhood days. Try an amazing platform to get in touch and meet new people. Straight forward app to use. Great design and information hierarchy. User friendly app that provides great experience to the user to form meaningful connections.

wowowow i just wanna say i love this app so much. It such a nice app! You get the experience again of when the internet became a bit popular. people just going online to meet new people and share interesting things about themselves. Great app, great concept. However, since last few updates, it's frustrating to use. Screen freezes, keyboard doesn't show sometimes, marker for text selection keeps appearing for no reason. Pretty fun app that brings back the good old days of writing letter to pen pals. Really slows down the pace of life and allow enjoyment of 'countryside life' in the city.

The idea is there but the execution is lacking. Two issues make this app a negative experience. First: Actually the text editor. Being able to select and delete a section of your letter just doesn't work reliably. It often deletes significantly more or less than your selection or lags. Second: Not being able to reference the letter you're replying to while writing. It makes it difficult to respond without pasting their letter in your draft and deleting as you go. Refer to problem one.

I love this app absolutely. The concept of writing to people with a delay is wonderful. A really cool app that I was looking for since long. I came from old times of pen-pal time and enjoy this kind of communication very much. Currently, for me instant chat kinda disturp the imagination that was offered by the letter as people already expecting to get reply really fast and only basic chit chat when knowing other peoples. This app offer the experience of telling stories that people not expecting to be replied fast. I live the Idea of the letter is taking diffefent time to arrived in different country and it is perfect for me. The one thing that I hope to be fixed is that sometime when I get to the home screen, It so slow and show nothing at all. Otherwise it is great experience.

I've only been using Slowly for a couple of days but I love the concept! The app is nicely designed and simple to use with no ads to disrupt your experience. The wait time between sending and receiving means you have chance to get excited waiting for a reply. You can also collect stamps from your friends around the world which is fun. A refreshing break from the mindlessness of instant messaging.

I really like the idea, I've already met some cool people. It's fun to take this letter approach to communication, we don't experience this much anymore. One thing about the app itself: sometimes when the app is still in the recents menu, and you try to open it from there it's stuck on the intro screen. That's the only complaint that I have. Cheers to the developers for making a great app!

I absolutely love this app. The only thing I would say could be fixed are the arrival times of messages and interest selections. The idea of the letter being sent under the stimulated time frame is amazing. However, I feel the time is too long. I think if the time was cut in half it would be more beneficial. I also think that everyone should be matched based upon personality and interests. There should be more room to learn about the person while having basic understanding. Other than that this app is amazing.

This got to be the most simple and effective app i've used, its exciting and fun, you can trade letters with someone from another country, and share your experience, culture and likes, the fun thing is you dont know what they look like. And the letter act like a literal snail mail, it takes time to arrive which makes you look forward on something. I already have penpal from italy, turkey, singapore, brazil and i just used this app yesterday, if ypu need someone to to talk, i recommend this app

I really recommend this app! I downloaded it only because I was trying to find something to do during the middle of class, but it stuck with me for almost a month! It really tests your patience to wait for a letter that takes up to 2 days for you to wait, but the waiting was worth it! It really does give you that sense of excitement of getting a letter, especially when we're in an era where you could've just emailed someone and get an answer right away. I LOVE THIS!

Exactly what I was looking for. Just a few days using it and I've already exchanged mails with a couple of people from very far away locations.  It perfectly brings back the experience of having pen pals around the world.  The interface is clean and provides a great user experience.  Without doubt, one of my favorites apps.  I'd love some functionalities to be added: 1) Landscape support (screen rotation): when you're writing with a Bluetooth keyboard, it might be easier to do it with the screen on landscape mode. 2) When writing replies, it'd be useful to be able to split the screen, so we could write in one area and read previous letters in the other one.

I really love the app and already have some nice pen pals from around the world. The stamp collection feature is super cool and adorable! Unfortunately I already received my first letter about dating and I'm really not interested in that. Would be nice to turn such letters off. (But it's great that picture sending needs consent from both parties)

So this is a Letter app. LETTER. Not instant chat. I realize that but took me a while to realize that I should've use a letter concept of communicating. And it's quite fun. Exchanging letters to the people you write with. I actually like how it takes hours to actually send and receive the letter from around the world. Exactly like mailing. Also, there are just too many unactive users. You guys should deactivate their accounts since them themselves wouldn't. And why is there so many users from the same country on my match making list? For example 4/5 users there are from China. Where are the other countries? Note that I did adjust the filter for which country I accept and which I don't. I hope you'll look into this.

Interesting idea. Still exploring the features. Would be great if you could expand the languages options - I'd like to have Arabic and Hebrew, unfortunately both are unavailable. Edit: languages selections have been improved which is great. However, those written from right to left have display issues under a user's language profile. Please fix.

Great concept, beautiful design. I'm using an Android tablet with physical keyboard, so missing an option for landscape mode is a big drawback, especially for an app that is made for writing. I know the option is under development, so I'm looking forward. It would also be handy an option to sort on top messages that I have not replied yet. Also no ads, no IAPs, this is awesome, thanks!

Pen-pal & stamps fascinated me to download this app. Initially when I had joined this app. I had sent 3 letters to the default picked users. I haven't received any response from them. Atleast there should be an option like the letter has been received but not interested to be a friend. Because some will just install & uninstall in the next moment. & some might end up waiting & get bored or uninstall it. Second thing that annoyed my is zodiac sign. I cannot change it. So I have hidden it. There should be an option to edit it. Rest everything is good about this app.

Genius app for those people who loves the idea of writing letters. Super excited using it and hoping it'll have the attention it deserves. Also, the only thing I see that needs improvement is the font. I wish there are various or few handwritten fonts just to make it feel real. But overall I love it!!!‚ô°‚ô°‚ô°

I don't usually share and recommend apps, but recently I tried this one and I'm having lots of fun and success meeting really cool people with similar interests. As someone who really likes to meet new people from around the world, I'm impressed to have connected with people in the USA, Japan, Korea, South Africa, and Myanmar so far! Basically, it's a pen pal app (not a dating app in any way)! You can connect to different people around the world, but it's like writing a letter rather than instant messaging. Based on the distance between countries, the "letter" takes time to arrive. I haven't had any creeps because there's no profile pictures, just avatars so you can focus on interests, which you can select in the beginning and get matched with similar people. It's kinda fun to wait for the "snail mail" because you end up writing more, like an email, but your talking with strangers based on common interests.

It actually is what it says...slow. Sometimes I consider too slow but I knew what was downloading. Actually, the fact that there is no profile picture makes it easy for ugly trolls like me to make friends not based on our appearance but common interests.

I must say I am quite pleasantly suprised by concept of app. I only wanted to give a whirl, because other alike apps have quickly became wade. Reason would be community itself, half of the time. I am at stage of life where I am tired of building reputation, fancy bio or trying to appeal to the majority in order to meet anyone. I am simple and direct. The way I express myself often also does not appeal to people. So the fact I can do express myself, pick the interest I want, give short and fundamental introduction and a top of all that see more alike real people on this app is amazing. And also the app is gem itself. It kind of brings old fashioned way people used to meet, with masks off. And it has very nice appeal to functionality and aesthetic. It's very unique concept, and nice community.

I absolutely love this app! There are perks in every aspect of it that I love and have been looking for that you'll have trouble finding in this day and age since instant messaging. It takes 1-2 days for a letter to reach you depends on the distance of where you and they live (much like an actual letter in the mail). I also like that it has the options to choose where you want to communicate with people in which country, by interests, etc. Plus, so far the conversations I've had are not small talk. I hate small talk. There is only 1 thing so far I wish they would add....designed (fun print) paper (or fonts)...something that gives the letters more character. Like holiday designs, space, clouds, baked goods, abstract or birthday types, something creative and simple. Even something like a floral print on the edges. I think this would really add character and more value to the app. This way people can express themselves not only in words.

Honestly an amazing app. Did not think I would enjoy it as much as I have been. First was a little irritated no one had responded yet but I later realized it's a waiting game just like real life mailing. Absolutely loved it! Really amazing concept 10/10
I love the concept, but currently no drafts are being saved. This makes it very difficult to write longer letters. As soon as you exit writing a letter without sending, you lose everything! :(.

I love this idea! At first I was skeptical about how long it would take to send the letter but it really weeds out the people who don't want to actually talk to you so you can meet some really good people! The only thing I would change change is when you look for a penpal if you want to talk to someone to help teach you another language from what I can tell you don't know if they speak your language or just the one you're trying to learn.

I love the idea, it brings back the anxiety of waiting the letter to arrive and excitement when it does arrives... It also makes you really think about what you write before sending, not only because they cannot be deleted and/or edited afterward but because it takes so long for them to get delivered! All in all I really recommend

A great app that gives you an opportunity to experience the beauty of slow communication in the world that is determined as fast. The beauty of sending the letters is back, and you can also put a virtual stamp on. There's no communication based on the way you look, the only relevant thing is topics that u have: so I can responsibly say it is quite a revolutionary road of the virtual communication these days.

After the update, the app has become really glitchy. Sometimes, it doesn't show incoming messages, takes a long time to open, doesn't show new messages. It always says 'no incoming messages at this moment' when I have 3. Please fix this.

Update : The community is unfortunately dead. You guys can definitely remind someone when they get a message. Even I end up checking it after 7-8 days. Slowly, the concept is really good. Thing is once you get talking to someone, this starts feeling like a chore really fast. Even if you are on constant chats with someone it takes 2 days to deliver the message to them. The gimmick wears off when you really want to talk to someone. Apart from that, there should be a system to keep encouraging people to write more, the amount of people I was connected with stop using it because it is not engaging enough. Plus, add some notifications!

Well, this was a quaint idea. I love it, and I would love to buy you guys a coffee if I had a card. I just wish that the waiting time was cut down by two or three hours. I know that's part of the app, but still. Also, Jamaica needs a stamp!üò£

In the era of instant everything, this app is a relief and an oasis. It's only once I used it that I realized that I'm so used to getting instant replies to any communication, that I need to work on the lost art of letter writing. The wait time was jarring at first but I really enjoy it now. The anticipation makes the incoming letter all the more rewarding.

It is a great application for those who like writing. Postcards have cool designs. I was surprised that there were designs for my country as well. BUT. Developers, please add a postcard with Flame Towers to the profile of Azerbajan. There is no excuse to avoid including them.
The age filter doesn't seem to work. I still see people outside of the range I set. Doesn't always exit properly. Leave the app on the screen and doesn't close. Have to shutdown to clear.

SLOWLY is wonderful. In a few short weeks I've met a ton of interesting people from all around the world! I occasionally experience glitches when the app is starting up, but other than that, this app does a fantastic job executing on a great concept.

It would be nice to have more than 100 penpals at the same time. Also please make it so we can still receive mesaages from people we have removed from the list. Some of the filtering is not as detailed as expected.

The concept is pretty cool, i like how we wait to get a new letter or send a letter to people. It is a pleasure to feel the old things i never do before. Keep developing this app and promote this app, to gain more user - youtube ads would do! Or endorsement

God, I love this app! It's simple and exciting and everything at once! I have always been wanted to send postcard all around the world, but I am a nomaden that it worries me that the postcard wont be able to reach me and yep this app is the answer to my misery!

This app is genuinely really fun. It doesn't take long before people from all over the world start sending letters, and I've found that it's very low pressure when you're replying. As somebody who gets incredibly nervous about talking to people, this app is fantastic!

I'm using this app for less than a month, and it's already my favourite app ever. It's something I wanted for a long time. An a app to meet genuine friends that not based on looks o whatever. I also love the fact that there is no ads of any type. I'm serious thinking of making my first donation ever

Just sent my first letter to 3 randomly matched friends, each from Belgium, Oman, and Trinidad&Tobago. I haven't even heard of the last two countries and had to google them. It's so exciting!!!! And I already got an incoming message from Italy! It's gonna arrive in a day. I get it that it's slow, but isn't that part of the charm of this app?

Download this. Seriously. Absolutely love this app. I've never experienced having a pen-pal and it's so amazing that I can finally experience it. Every single minute waiting for the arrival of the letters was worth it and it was so fun being able to talk to people in the same country as you and connecting with them.
Great concept! The only problem is this app needs to clean those people who just tried this app for once and then gave up. People need to make friends just the real ones! Rest all good

Slowly is an application to connect with people from around the world while reconnecting with your ability to get excited about delaying gratification. While I haven't used the app for very long, I am legitimately excited to open the letters I receive after waiting for them to arrive.

1. No ads - perfect! Thank you so much for creating this wonderful app without annoying ads 2. Letter delivery - I think it's genius that the letters take hours to receive. GOLD. Thank you for bringing this back.

I miss the age of pen pals and this app helps you relive that era. I've started talking to people from all around the world and absolutely love it. It's quick and easy. Within a week I already have 10 different pen pals. I definitely recommend this app.
It's awesome! Having a letter delivered "slowly" kind of takes away the awkwardness of trying to make conversation when you first meet someone. There are lots of friendly people too.
Absolutely Love this app. I do wish you could request to send images from the latter screen instead of having to go to the profile, but that's just being picky. 5 stars for sure.

In this time when there is over saturation of social media apps, Slowly def made itself standout. This probably is one of the best platforms for meaningful convos and learning about the world minus the nonsense bs like 'you already know' apps.
It's such a great app. We can make friends around the globe and can know about their culture and so much more. I ain't receiving any letter though it's a nice app
I just got the app about 3 days ago. So far so good! I've always liked penpal relationships. It's sad that letters are becoming so obsolete now. It's nice to bring it back.

Slowly is an app allowing you to write letters to anyone in the world about anything you want to. The beauty in the app comes from the fact that the letters arrive based on the actual time it takes for a letter to arrive. Guess if you were using AusPost you're screwed (dum tish). The positive of this app is that it doesn't actually use paper. You can send letters with stamps and start with a small collection based on your geographical location. I really enjoy this app. It's not intrusive with a million notifications and it respects your privacy. You both have to mutually agree to share images to do so. When you launch the app you can choose several interests and languages, even stating your fluency in the language (even if it is nothing!). The app has preset profile images meaning you don't have to upload one of yourself and the art style is really cute. The stamp collection is very cute too. The colour scheme of slowly is minimalistic and pleasing, using colours to not exclude those with colour blindness. Unfortunately you cannot adjust the letter size. You are able to save some letter drafts to send to a couple of people if you'd like and you can also refer to the letter you just received to know What you're replying to. I recommend this app to anyone who wants to make friends. It's really fun and simple, and connecting with people globally speaking in a language that neither of you have as your first is so fulfilling.

It's a great idea, and a great app. While it seems new and lacks a few very minor features, such as additional inbox(recently received section) formats (there's only one layout, and I kinda don't like it), and lacks options such as mark as unread, snooze, etc, it gets the job done, quickly easily and efficiently. There are a few minor issues I wish to point out. One of then would be the lack of features mentioned above, and the about me section. It seems that I am the only person who can see it. While when writing mail, it is quite normal to not have a about me section, I don't see a real reason for it to be there. Additionally, I think it's good to let us see the about me section of other users, since we are writing to complete strangers, which does not happen when writing actual mail. I also think the lack of stamps is a real problem, as it stifles variety and expression of emotions. Moreover, its not apparent how we are to use our stamps. I found out eventually, but I've been using this app for 3-4 days, and all my pen pals use the default stamp. While I love that you can change the stamp just by tapping on it, it might be too subtle for many to notice, and I think it should be included in the user guide. I think it's still a new feature, and the shop is still expanding, but I would hate it if we have buy 90% of the stamps we use. Just pointing that out. However, I do understand the app has to make money somehow. Ads? Maybe. Or I'd just buy you a coffeeüòâ Overall, great app! Gives people the chance to write actually meaningful stuff, and appreciate communicating(it's been a long time since I had to think long and hard about what to write!(if I ever did) ). Really cool app for sending messages that are delayed by several hours-- up 
to several days, even. One of my problems is that I try to match with 
people who have been on recently and get people who haven't been online in 
months. Another problem is I'm not sure if this is the type of app people 
try and then get rid of because it's too slow, therefore rendering my 
messages unread or cause conversations to end prematurely. My suggestion is 
to have some sort of tracking system that gives you more than just a "you 
have no/multiple letters incoming" heads up, such as "your letter will be 
received in x amount of time" and "your letter has been opened" all in the 
same place as the "you have incoming". Just ideas though.
